    <h2>PREPARED FOR SUCCESS</h2>
    <h5><strong>Our students work hard for... a competitive, high quality education</strong></h5>
    <ul>
      <li>• Our volunteer teachers hold MA degrees, and have completed ESL training. They come from around the world, and bring a global perspective to the classroom. We've had superb teachers from such disparate places as: China, Ireland, the United States, Mexico, and Australia.</li>
      <li>• Mungere students consistently score in the top quarter of schools in the region and in the top 2 in the district (out of 10 schools) in government issued tests.</li>
      <li>• The Tanzania Ministry of Education has recognized Red Sweater Project as a successful school model that gets results.
      an atmosphere that promotes gender equality</li>
      <li>• Boys and girls learn together in the classrooms, and in our athletics program. This approach builds the confidence of female students, and teaches all of the students that everyone has strengths, and they are not defined or limited by gender. </li>
    </ul>
    <h5><strong>Sustainably designed, modern facilities</strong></h5>
    <ul>
      <li>• Solar power throughout campus has been made possible by the volunteer efforts of Engineers without Borders</li>
      <li>• Individual solar-powered lanterns for students to use for late night studying</li>
      <li>• Buildings designed to keep students and faculty cool in the heat and warm when it's cold out without the use of consumable fuels.</li>
    </ul>
    <h5><strong>Health care, health education, and sanitation services</strong></h5>
    <ul>
      <li>• Clean drinking water is available for all students</li>
      <li>• Health outreach helps to boost health and prevent disease within the community</li>
      <li>• If a student gets sick, they're treated. Some of the illnesses commonly treated include: malaria, typhoid and pneumonia</li>
      <li>• Fresh, nutritious food from our organic school garden and dining facilities, which serves two meals each school day</li>
      <li>• Campus is equipped with composting toilets and handwashing stations</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
